在日本，《超執刀 神使之杖》未能登上[[Fami通|Fami通]]2005年頭500名銷量排行榜，而最後一名的銷量估算為15,000分，暗示該遊戲賣出的份量更少。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://geimin.net/da/db/2005_ne_fa/|script-title=ja:2005年テレビゲームソフト売り上げTOP500|trans_title=2005年遊戲銷量500強|language=ja|website=Geimin.net|access-date=2016-04-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160415125007/http://geimin.net/da/db/2005_ne_fa/|archive-date=2016-04-15|dead-url=yes}}</ref>相反，Atlus USA銷售副總監Jim Ireton指出英文版在北美的表現「非常優秀」，銷量「超乎想像」。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gamedeveloper.com/business/mapping-the-world-with-atlus-jim-ireton-on-atlus-import-aspirations|title=Mapping The World With Atlus: Jim Ireton on Atlus' Import Aspirations|trans_title=和Atlus解讀大局：Jim Ireton對Atlus外來遊戲的願景|language=en|last=Anderson|first=John|website=[[Gamasutra|Game Developer]]|date=2006-02-06|access-date=2015-08-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141111034728/http://www.gamasutra.com/view/feature/130949/mapping_the_world_with_atlus_jim_.php|archive-date=2014-11-11|dead-url=no}}</ref>遊戲受歡迎的程度令Atlus USA決定在2006年7月向電玩店補貨。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2006/06/27/trauma-center-resuscitated|title=Trauma Center Resuscitated|trans_title=《超執刀 神使之杖》再再創佳績|language=en|website=[[IGN|IGN]]|date=2006-06-27|access-date=2018-11-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121228080718/https://www.ign.com/articles/2006/06/27/trauma-center-resuscitated|archive-date=2012-12-28|dead-url=no}}</ref>該遊戲在歐洲銷量同樣出色。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eurogamer.net/news090806traumacenterwii|title=Trauma Center for Wii launch|trans_title=《超執刀 神使之杖》和Wii同步發售|language=en|last=Gibson|first=Ellie|website=[[Eurogamer|Eurogamer]]|date=2006-08-09|access-date=2018-11-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160714062055/https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/news090806traumacenterwii|archive-date=2016-07-14|dead-url=no}}</ref>雖然Atlus在2006年前幾年的財政狀況不佳，該遊戲的海外銷量令公司賺到利潤。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rpgfan.com/news/2006/1572.html|title=Index Becomes Atlus' New Parent Company|trans_title=Index控股收購Atlus|language=en|last=Winkler|first=Chris|website=RPGFan|date=2006-11-27|access-date=2018-11-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070510162152/http://www.rpgfan.com/news/2006/1572.html|archive-date=2007-05-10|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

